subSubSection.paragraph:
This species occurs in lower elevations of South Africa and Mozambique , close to the coast of the Indian Ocean. Some males have been attracted in the late morning hours using artificial pheromones. Zhang (1994) mentions sweet potato (
Ipomoea batatas
) as hostplant of this species as well.
